Zone-redundant gateways are deployed across multiple availability zones within a region to ensure high availability.

These gateways automatically distribute traffic across zones, reducing the risk of failure due to a single zone outage.

For example, a VPN or ExpressRoute gateway can be configured as zone-redundant.

A real-life use case is enterprise networking where uptime is critical.

Another example is applications requiring high availability across zones.

Zone redundancy enhances resilience and fault tolerance.
